{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57a2f5e2-0c2d-4443-8cef-82d22adc1f0d","content":"Let me also check the broader project structure to see if there's a `.nuspec` or `.csproj` for packaging.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GAUWTuPHVQ436JvKpwXYhH","name":"view","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-3a23559ab7014ff78361ef866cec688a"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"view the file at /tmp/sv-3a23559ab7014ff78361ef866cec688a."}],"interactionId":"10ee8951-13c5-4aa8-a68a-5b5d5cdbe132","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. Let me check for required and recommended fields.\n\nKey issues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not strictly required but highly recommended for validation.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for template packs with multiple related templates.\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of the same template are installed.\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Common best practice for project templates.\n5. **Missing `defaultName`** — The default project name when none is specified.\n6. The `sourceName` replacement — this looks fine.\n\n\n7. **`classifications`** and **`tags`** look good, but there's a critical issue with the Framework symbol — it's missing a `replaces` property, so the framework choice won't actually substitute the `<TargetFramework>` element in the project file.\n\nI should check what other files are in the template package to get a better sense of the overall structure.","outputTokens":359},"id":"d5c5cdc1-7b70-4221-a2fb-3327e8f24ff2","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:43:13.219Z","parentId":"cd1ac90b-a11a-4ff2-8b5c-ff72d32f2504"}
